title: In Arizona’s Race for Governor, Hobbs Takes a Narrow Lead
description: The Democratic candidate’s mild manner has been a counterweight to her rival Kari Lake’s charismatic and antagonistic style.
dc:creator: Jazmine Ulloa

media:content.media:credit: Caitlin O'Hara for The New York Times
media:content.media:description: Katie Hobbs, Arizona’s secretary of state and the Democrats’ candidate for governor, in Mesa, Ariz., on Monday.
